msgid "In the <placeholder-1/> eclass there are functions which provide installation facilities for <placeholder-2/> files (<placeholder-3/> and <placeholder-4/>, whose usage is the same as similar <placeholder-5/> and <placeholder-6/> functions) and the <placeholder-7/> files (<placeholder-8/> and <placeholder-9/>, which need the first argument to be the subdirectory of <placeholder-10/> in which the files are to be installed). Those groups of functions already takes care of verifying whether the <placeholder-11/> USE flag is made optional for the package <d/> if this is the case, and the flag is disabled, the <placeholder-12/> files are just skipped."
