#: devmanual/tasks-reference/pam/text.xml:210(p)
msgid "Many <placeholder-1/> files just uses one or more auth types from <placeholder-2/> login class, which is the base one which provides login facilities for most services on common desktop systems. Instead of adding a <placeholder-3/> file in <placeholder-4/> for this, one can use the <placeholder-5/> function. This function takes a series of parameters <d/> the first one is the name of the login class (the name of the <placeholder-6/> file in /etc/pam.d); the others are the auth types for which system-auth needs to be used."
